Description: Smart, personalized advice for every parent.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Village is an early stage startup with a mission to help moms and dads everywhere live simpler, happier lives. Why? Because parenting is hard work. You go into it with little or no training and the stakes are really high. Worst of all, there's no singular place to find tried-and-true wisdom to help you make decisions about where to spend your time, money and energy. Village is a knowledge marketplace for parents. They're building a platform to aggregate, organize and personalize parenting wisdom for families everywhere. Their mobile app allows users to submit questions, which are then directed to moms and dads in similar stages of life, so every answer is empathetic and relevant. Description: Wooster Self Storage is a leading self-storage facility
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Wooster Self Storage is a leading self-storage facility located in Wooster, Ohio. We offer secure, clean, and affordable storage solutions to individuals, families, and businesses in and around our community.  At Wooster Self Storage, we understand that modern life can be demanding and unpredictable. With space becoming increasingly scarce and the number of belongings we accumulate on a daily basis mounting, it can be tough to find a place to store everything. That's where we come in.  We provide our customers with a vast array of storage options to suit every need, from small lockers to large units capable of storing a full house's worth of items. Whatever your storage needs, we have a solution that will work for you.  Our facility is open seven days a week, offering convenient access to your stored items whenever you need them. We also offer extended hours during peak moving and holiday seasons to ensure our customers can access their belongings when they need to.  Our state-of-the-art security system ensures your peace of mind and the safety of your belongings. Our facility is fully fenced and gated, and we utilize 24/7 video surveillance to monitor the premises. Additionally, our unique access system ensures that only authorized individuals are permitted on-site.  We take pride in keeping our facility clean and well-maintained. Our team of professionals work hard to ensure that the grounds and units are clean, dry, and free from pests. We also prioritize customer satisfaction, and our friendly and knowledgeable staff will assist you with any questions or concerns you may have.  At Wooster Self Storage, we understand that our customers' belongings are valuable and important to them. That's why we offer some of the most affordable rates in the industry without skimping on quality. We believe that everyone should have access to safe, clean, and convenient storage options, regardless of their financial situation.  Whether you're moving to a new home, renovating your current space, or simply need extra space to store your belongings, Wooster Self Storage has the perfect solution for you. Our variety of unit sizes and options cater to a wide range of needs and budgets.  We pride ourselves on our commitment to customer satisfaction and convenience. That's why we offer online bill payment and account management, making it easy to stay on top of your storage needs from the comfort of your own home. We also offer flexible leasing options, allowing you to adjust your storage space or duration as your needs change.  In summary, Wooster Self Storage is the premier storage facility in Wooster, Ohio. We offer secure, clean, and affordable storage solutions to meet the needs of individuals, families, and businesses. Our state-of-the-art security system, friendly staff, and commitment to customer satisfaction make us the ideal choice for all your storage needs.

The word comes from Huki, meaning pull, and lau, meaning leaves. A large number of people, usually family and friends, would work together in casting the net from shore and then pulling it back. The net was lined with ki leaves, which would help scare the fish into the center of the net. Consistent with the Hawaiian subsistence economy, anybody that helped could share in the catch.
